- Sony (Alpha 1, A9 III, A7S III, A7 IV with firmware)
- Nikon (Z6 III firmware planned for 2025)

**Media Organizations**:

- Reuters (pilot program with Canon prototype cameras) [thomsonreuters](https://www.thomsonreuters.com/en/press-releases/2023/august/reuters-new-proof-of-concept-employs-authentication-system-to-securely-capture-store-and-verify-photographs)
- BBC and ARD (broadcast verification implementations) [aws.amazon](https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/media/ard-ensures-content-provenance-with-c2pa-and-aws/)
- CBC/Radio-Canada (video authenticity documentation) [aws.amazon](https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/media/cbc-radio-canada-documents-video-authenticity-with-content-credentials-on-aws/)

**Technology Platforms**:

